<P><Q><HI>And the Woman &s;aid, the Serpent beguiled me, and I did eat.</HI></Q> She does not make u&s;e of &s;o many Words to excu&s;e her&s;elf, as her Hu&s;band; but her Heart is as unhumbled as his&mdash;What is this, &s;ays God, that thou ha&s;t done? God here charges her with doing it.&mdash;She dares not deny the Fact, or &s;ay, I have not done it&punc; but &s;he takes all the Blame off her&s;elf, and lay<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> it upon the Serpent&mdash;<Q><HI>The Serpent beguiled me and I did eat.</HI>&mdash;She does not &s;ay, Lord, I was to blame for talking with the Serpent<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc; Lord, I did wrong, in not ha&s;ting to my Hu&s;band, when he put the fir&s;t Que&s;tion to me&mdash;Lord, I plead guilty, I only am to blame&mdash;Oh, let not my poor Hu&s;band &s;uffer for my Wickedne&s;s!</Q>&mdash;This would have been the Language of her Heart, had &s;he now been a true Penitent. But both were now <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">like proud&mdash;Therefore neither will lay <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> upon <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;<Q><HI>The Serpent beguiled me, and I did
