<P>This Promi&s;e was literally fulfilled in the Per|&s;on of our Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t&mdash;Satan brui&s;ed his Heel, when he tempted him for forty Days together in the Wilderne&s;s&mdash;He brui&s;ed his Heel, when he rai&s;ed up &s;trong Per&s;ecution again&s;t him, during the Time of his publick Mini&s;try&mdash;He, in an e&s;pecial Manner, brui&s;ed his Heel, when our Lord complained, that his <HI>Soul was exceeding &s;orrowful, even unto Death <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> and he &s;weat great Drops of Blood falling upon the Ground,</HI> when praying in the Garden&mdash;He brui&s;ed his Heel, when he put it into the Heart of <HI>Judas</HI> to betray him:&mdash;And he brui&s;ed him yet mo&s;t of all, when his Emi&s;&s;aries nailed him to an accur&s;ed Tree, and our Lord cried out, <HI>My God, my God, why ha&s;t thou for&s;aken one?</HI>&mdash;Ye<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">; in all this, the ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us, the <HI>Seed of the Woman,</HI> brui&s;ed his accur&s;ed Head&mdash;For, in that he was tempted, he was able to <HI>&s;uccour tho&s;e that are tempted.</HI> By <HI>his Stripes we are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc;</HI> The Cha&s;ti&s;ement of our Peace was
