<PB N="53" REF="005311_0060_10180FFD5E512B60">
in his Time to a mowed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ield, the more fre|quently it is cut, the more it grows.&mdash;The Blood of the Martyrs was always the Seed of the Church. And I have often &s;at down with Wonder and Delight, and admired how God has made the very Schemes, which his Enemies contrived in order to hinder, the mo&s;t effectual Means to propagate his Go&s;pel&mdash;The Devil h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">s had &s;o little Succe&s;s in Per&s;ecution, that if I did not know, that he and his Children, according to this Ver&s;e, could not but per&s;ecute, I &s;hould think he would count it his Strength to &s;it &s;till. What did he get by per&s;ecuting the Martyrs in&punc; Queen <HI>Mary'</HI>s Time?&mdash;Was not the Grace of God exceedingly glorified in their Support <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> What did he g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">t by per&s;ecuting the good old Puritants? Did it not prove the Peopleing o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>New-England?</HI>&mdash;Or, to come nearer to our own Times, What has he got by putting <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> out of the Synagogues? Hath not the Word of God, &s;ince that, mightily prevailed?&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> dear Hearers, you mu&s;t excu&s;e me for enlarging on this Head. God fills my Soul generally when I come to this Topick. I can &s;ay <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; <HI>Luther,</HI> <Q>If it were not for Per&s;ecution &s;hould not under&s;tand the Scripture&punc;</Q> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Satan &s;hould be yet &s;uffered to brui&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> further, and his Servants &s;hould thru&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Pri&s;on&punc; I doubt not, but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ven that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">|tend to the more <HI>effectual Brui&s;ing of his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc;</HI> I remember a Saying of the then Lord Chan|cellor to the pious <HI>Bradford.</HI> <Q>Thou <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> done more Hurt, &s;aid he, by thy Exhorta|tions
<PB N="54" REF="005311_0061_10180FFEF5217890">
in private in Pri&s;on, than thou did&s;t in preaching before thou wa&s;t put in,</Q> or Words to this Effect. The Promi&s;e of the Text is my daily Support. <HI>I will put Enmity between thy Seed and her Seed; it &s;hall brui&s;e thy Head, and thou &s;halt brui&s;e his Heel.</HI>&mdash;</P>
<P>Further: This Promi&s;e is al&s;o fulfilled, not only in the Church in general, but in every in|dividual Believer in particular&mdash;In every Belie|ver there are two Seeds, the <HI>Seed of the Woman,</HI> and the <HI>Seed of the Serpent</HI>&mdash;The Fle&s;h lu&s;ting again&s;t the Spirit, and the Spirit again&s;t the Fle&s;h.&mdash;It is with the Believer, when quickned with Grace in his Heart, as it was with <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">,</HI> when &s;he had conceived <HI>E&s;au</HI> and <HI>Jacob</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> her Womb! She felt a Struggling, and began to be unea&s;y.&mdash;<HI>If it be &s;o,</HI> &s;ays &s;he, <HI>why am I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">?</HI>&mdash;Thus Grace and Nature &s;truggle, (if <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> may &s;o &s;peak) in the Womb of a Believer's Heart&mdash;But, as it was there &s;aid, the Elder &s;hall <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the Younger; &s;o it is here&mdash;Grace in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">nd &s;hall get the better of Nature&mdash;The <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the Woman &s;hall brui&s;e the Serpent's <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">. Many of you perhaps, that have be|lieved in Chri&s;t, may find &s;ome particular Cor|ruption yet &s;trong, &s;o &s;trong, that you are &s;ome|times ready to cry out with <HI>David, I &s;hall fail <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the Hand of Saul</HI>&mdash;But, fear not, the Promi&s;e in the Text in&s;ures the P<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">rl<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ve <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> and Victory of Believers over Sin, Satan Death and Hell.&mdash;What if indwelling Corrup|tion does yet remain, and the Seed of the Ser|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="4 letters"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> your Heel, in vexing and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">
<PB N="55" REF="005311_0062_10181000F67E60E0">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> righteous Souls? Fear not, tho' <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">aint, yet <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">r&s;ue You &s;hall yet brui&s;e the Serpent's Head. Chri&s;t hath died for you, and yet a little while, and he will &s;end Death to de&s;troy the very Being of Sin in you.&mdash;Which brings me</P>
<P>To &s;hew the mo&s;t exten&s;ive Manner in which the Promi&s;e of the Text &s;hall be fulfilled, <HI>viz.</HI> at the final Judgment, when the Lord Je&s;us &s;hall pre&s;ent the Elect to his Father without Spot or Wrinkle, or any &s;uch Thing, glorified both in Body and Soul.&mdash;</P>
<P>Then &s;hall the Seed of the Woman give the la&s;t and fatal Blow, in brui&s;ing the Serpent's Head&mdash;Satan, the Accu&s;er of the Brethren, and all his accur&s;ed Seed, &s;hall then be ca&s;t out; and never &s;uffered to di&s;turb the Seed of the Wo|man any more&mdash;Then &s;hall the Righteous &s;hine in the Kingdom of their Father, and fit with Chri&s;t on Thrones, in Maje&s;ty on High.</P>
<P>Let us therefore not be weary of Well-doing for we &s;hall reap an eternal Harve&s;t of Comfort, if we faint not.&mdash;Dare, dare, my dear Brethren in Chri&s;t, to follow the Captain of your Salva|tion, who was made perfect through Sufferings. The Seed of the Woman &s;hall brui&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Ser|pent's Head&mdash;Fear not Men&mdash;Be not too <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> ca&s;t down at the Deceitfulne&s;s of your Heart<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Fear not Devils&mdash;You &s;hall get the Victory <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> over them&mdash;The Lord Je&s;us has engaged to make you more than Conqueror over all&mdash;Plead with your Saviour, plead&mdash;Plead the Promi&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n in the Text&mdash;Wre&s;tle, wre&s;tle with God in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;If it has been given you to believe, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ear
<PB N="56" REF="005311_0063_10181005C8B4E5A8">
not, if it &s;hould al&s;o be given you to &s;uffer. Be not any wi&s;e terrified by your Adver&s;aries&mdash;The King of the Church has them all in a Chain&mdash;Be kind to them; pray for them; but fear them not. The Lord will yet bring back his Ark, tho' at pre&s;ent driven into the Wilderne&s;s, and Satan like Lightning &s;hall fall from Heaven.</P>
<P>Are there any Enemies of God here? The Promi&s;e of the Text encourages me to bid you Defiance&mdash;The <HI>Seed of the Woman,</HI> the <HI>ever-ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us &s;hall brui&s;e the Serpent's Head</HI>&mdash;What &s;ignifies all your Malice&mdash;You are only raging Waves of the Sea, foaming out your <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Shame&mdash;For you, without Repentance, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the Blackne&s;s of Darkne&s;s for ever&mdash;The Lord Je&s;us &s;its in Heaven ruling over all, and cau&s;ing all Things to work for his Childrens Good&mdash;He laughs you to &s;corn&mdash;He hath you in the utmo&s;t Deri&s;ion, and therefore &s;o will I&mdash;Who a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e you that per&s;ecute the Children of the ever-ble&s;&s;ed God?&mdash;Tho' a poor Stripling, the Lord Je&s;us, <HI>the Seed of the Woman,</HI> will enable <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to brui&s;e your Heads.</P>
<P>My Brethren in Chri&s;t, I think I do not &s;peak <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in my own Strength, but in the Strength of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Redeemer&mdash;I know in whom I have be|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ered&mdash;I am per&s;uaded he will keep that &s;afe which I have committed unto him&mdash;He is faithful who hath promi&s;ed, <HI>that the Seed of the Woman &s;hall brui&s;e the Serpent's Head</HI>&mdash;May we all experience a daily Completion
<PB N="57" REF="005311_0064_1018100783A05C28">
of this Promi&s;e, both in the Church and in our Hearts, till we come to the Church of the Fir&s;t-born, the Spirits of ju&s;t Men made <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in the Pre&s;ence and actual Fruition of the great God, our heavenly Father.</P>
<P><HI>To whom with the Son and the Holy Gho&s;t, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Honour, Power, Might, Maje&s;ty and Dominion, now and for evermore.</HI> Amen.</P>
