<P>But what does God &s;ay to <HI>Abraham? Ver.</HI> 2. <Q><HI>Take now thy Son, thine only Son </HI> I&s;aac, <HI>whom thou love&s;t, and get thee into the Land of</HI> M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">riah, <HI>and offer him there for a Burnt-offering upon one of the Mountains which I &s;hall tell thee of.</HI></Q></P>
<P>Every Word de&s;erves our particular Ob&s;er|vation&mdash;Whatever he was to do, he mu&s;t do it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, immediately, without conferring with Fle&s;h and Blood&mdash;But what mu&s;t he do? <HI>Take now thy Son</HI>&mdash;Had God &s;aid, take now a Fir&s;t|ling, or choice&s;t Lamb or Bea&s;t of thy Flock, and offer it up for a Burnt-offering, it would not have appeared &s;o gha&s;tly; but for God to &s;ay, <HI>Take now thy Son, and offer him up for a Burnt-offering,</HI> one would have imagined was enough to &s;tagger the &s;tronge&s;t Faith&mdash;But this is not all&mdash;It mu&s;t not only be a Son, but <HI>thine only Son</HI> I&s;aac, <HI>whom thou love&s;t</HI>&mdash;If it mu&s;t be a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> and not a Bea&s;t, that mu&s;t be offered, why <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>I&s;hmael</HI> do, the Son of the Bond-Wo|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> No, it mu&s;t be his <HI>only Son,</HI> the Heir of all Things, his <HI>I&s;aac,</HI> by Interpretation <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; the Son of his old Age, in whom his
