<P>And here let us pau&s;e a-while, and by Faith take a View of the Place where the Father has <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> him&mdash;I doubt not but the ble&s;&s;ed Angels <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> round the Altar and &s;ang, <HI>Glory be to God in the Highe&s;t,</HI> for giving &s;uch Faith to M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n&mdash;Come all ye tender-hearted Parents, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> what it is to look over a dying Child <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> that you &s;aw the Altar here erected before you, and th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> Wood laid in Order, and the beloved <HI>I&s;aac</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> upon it&mdash;Fancy that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;aw the aged Parent &s;tanding by weeping&mdash;(For why may we not &s;uppo&s;e that <HI>Abraham</HI> wept, &s;ince Je&s;us him&s;elf wept at the Grave of <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">z<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">us?</HI>)&mdash;Oh! what pious, endearing Ex|pre&s;&s;ions pa&s;&s;ed now alternately between the
