But &s;ing, O Heavens; and rejoice, O Earth! Man's Extremity is God's Opportunity&mdash;For behold, ju&s;t as the Knife, in all Probability, was near his Throat.&mdash;<HI>Ver.</HI> 11. <Q><HI>The Angel of the Lord,</HI> (or rather, the <HI>Lord of Angels,</HI> Je&s;us Chri&s;t, the Angel of the everla&s;ting Covenant) <HI>called unto him,</HI> probably in a very audible Manner, <HI>from Heaven</HI> (his Dwelling-Place) <HI>and &s;aid, Abraham, Abraham</HI>&mdash;(The Word is doubled to engage his Attention, and perhaps the Suddenne&s;s of the Call made him draw back his Hand, ju&s;t as he was go|ing to &s;trike his Son) <HI>And</HI> Abraham <HI>&s;aid Here am I</HI></Q>&mdash;</P>
<P><HI>And he &s;aid, (Ver.</HI> 12.) <HI>Lay not thine Hand upon the Lad, neither do thou any Thing unto him&mdash;For now know I that thou feare&s;t God, &s;eeing thou ha&s;t not with-held thy Son, thine only Son from me.</HI></P>
<P>Here then it was that <HI>Abraham</HI> received his Son <HI>I&s;aac</HI> from the Dead in a Figure&mdash;He was in effect offered upon the Altar, and God look'd upon him as offered and given unto him&mdash;Now it was that <HI>Abraham'</HI>s Faith being tried, was found more precious than Gold purified <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Times in the Fire&mdash;Now as a Reward of Grace&punc; tho' not of Debt, for this &s;ignal Act of Obedi|ence, by an Oath, God confirms the Promi&s;e he made to him long before, <HI>that in his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">tions of the Earth &s;hould be ble&s;&s;ed,</HI> was to be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> 8.</P>
<P><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> (this <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Comfort may we &s;uppo&s;e the <HI>I&s;aac&punc;</HI> was offend his Son went down from the
