<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> was &s;ealed in Heaven&mdash;And who <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> but you may be thus exalted before you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> if you humble your&s;elves? Oh, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Peace, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, and Joy, would you th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n feel <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> your Hearts&punc; You would have a Heaven upon E<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">th&mdash;Oh, that I could <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> any of you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> (as I once heard a poor Sinner under my Preaching cry out) <HI>He is come, He is come!</HI> How would you then, like him, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a precious Chri&s;t, a free-hearted Chri&s;t&punc; How would you magnify him for being &s;uch a Friend to <HI>Publicans</HI> and <HI>Sinners?</HI> Greater Love can no Man &s;hew, than to lay down his Life for a Friend&punc; But Chri&s;t laid down his Life for his Enemies&mdash;Even for you, if you are enabled to humble your&s;elves, as the <HI>Publican</HI> did&mdash;Sinners&punc; I know not how to leave off talking with you&mdash;I would fill my Mouth with Arguments&mdash;I would plead with you&mdash;<HI>Come, let us rea&s;on together</HI>&mdash;Tho' your Sins <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e as Scarlet, yet, if you humble your&s;elves, they &s;hall be as white as Snow&mdash;One Act of true <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in Chri&s;t ju&s;tifies you for ever and ever&punc; He h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> not promi&s;ed you what he cannot perform&mdash;He <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> able to exalt you&mdash;For God hath exalted, and given him a Name above every Name, that a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> the Name of Je&s;us every Knee &s;hall bow&mdash;Nay&punc; God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> him to be not only a Prince, but a Saviour <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> May he be a Saviour to you&punc; and then I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> have Rea&s;on to rejoice in the Day of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> preached in vain <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> laboured in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">.</P>
