<HEAD>SERMON VIII.</HEAD>
<HEAD>The Holy Spirit convincing the World of Sin, Righteou&s;ne&s;s, and Judgment.</HEAD>
<EPIGRAPH>
<BIBL>JOHN xvi. 8.</BIBL>
<Q><HI>And when he is come, he will reprove the World of Sin, and of Righteou&s;ne&s;s, and of Judgment.</HI></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<P>THESE Words contain Part of a gracious Promi&s;e which the ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us was plea&s;ed to make to his weeping and &s;or|rowful Di&s;ciples&mdash;The Time was now draw|ing near, in which the Son of Man was fir&s;t to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e lifted upon the Cro&s;s, and afterward to Hea|ven&punc; Kind&punc; Oh wondrous kind! had this mer|ciful High-Prie&s;t been to his Di&s;ciples during the Time of his tabernacling among&s;t them&mdash;He <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ad Compa&s;&s;ion on their Infirmities, an&s;wered for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">hem when a&s;&s;aulted by their Enemies, &amp; &s;et them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ight when out of the Way, either in Principle <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Practice&mdash;He neither called or u&s;ed them as
<PB N="175" REF="005311_0182_10181A84AE2FAB60">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Happened the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> under&s;tand <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the hidden <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of the Kingdom <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> God, when he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> others in Parabl<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&punc; Nay he became the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> all, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> conde&s;cended to wa&s;h their Feet&mdash;The Thoughts of parting with &s;o dear and loving a Ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">r as this, e&s;pe|cially for a long <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; mu&s;t needs affect them much&mdash;When <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> he in|tended to be a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;ent from them only for a Night, we are told, he was <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">train</HI> them to leave him&mdash;No wonder then, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> when he now informed them, he mu&s;t entirely go away, and that the <HI>Phari&s;ees</HI> in his Ab&s;ence &s;hould put them out of them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> &amp; ex<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">mmu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">cate <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> yea, that the Time &s;hould come, that who&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> ki<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ed them, &s;hould think <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> did God Set <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> (A Prophecy <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> would <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in an <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> Manner de&s;igned <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the &s;uffering Mini&s;ters of this Generation) No wonder, I &s;ay, con&s;idering all this&punc; that we are told, <HI>Ver.</HI> 6. That Sorrow had filled <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Hearts <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>Becau&s;e I have <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">hed <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the&s;e Times unto <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> and, Sorrow <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ath filled your Hear<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Heart were &s;o full of Concern, that they were <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">&mdash;In order therefore to reconcile them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Dis|pen&s;ation, our dear &amp; compa<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">nate Redeemer &s;hews them the Nece&s;&s;ity he lay under to leave them&mdash;<Q><HI>Neverthele&s;s, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></HI> he, <HI>I tell you the Truth; it is expedient for you that I go away:</HI></Q>
<PB N="176" REF="005311_0183_10181A879FF175B0">
As tho' he had &s;aid&mdash;Think not, my dear Di&s;|ciples, that I leave you out of Anger&mdash;No, it's for your Sakes, for your Profit, that I go away <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> For if I go not away, i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> I die not upon the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> for your Sins, and ri&s;e again for your Ju&s;tifica|tion, &amp; a&s;cend into Heaven to make Interce&s;&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> and plead my Merits before my Father's Throne, the Comforter, the Holy Gho&s;t, will not, can|not come unto you. But if I depart, I'll &s;end him unto you&mdash;And that they might know wha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> he was to do, <Q><HI>When he is come&punc;</HI> &s;ays our Lord, <HI>he will reprove the World of Sin, and of Righ|teou&s;ne&s;s, and of Judgment.</HI></Q></P>
<P>The Per&s;on then referred to in the Words of the Text, is plainly the Comforter, the Holy Gho&s;t, and the Promi&s;e was fir&s;t made to our Lord's Apo&s;tles&mdash;But tho' it was primarily made <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> them, and was literally and remarkably <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> at the Day of <HI>Pentico&s;t,</HI> when the Holy Gho&s;t came down, as a mighty ru&s;hing Wind and al&s;o when three thou&s;and were pricked to the Heart by <HI>Peter'</HI>s Preaching, yet as the A|po&s;tles were the Repre&s;entatives of the whole Body of Believers, we mu&s;t infer, that this Pro|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="4 letters"> mu&s;t be looked upon as &s;poken to us, and to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Children, and to as many as the Lord our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> call</P>
<P>M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> De&s;ign from the&s;e Words at pre&s;ent, is to &s;hew the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in which the Holy Gho&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> works upon the Hearts of tho&s;e, who, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Ve&s;&s;els of Mercy, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Kingdom of Darkne&s;s, into the Kingdom of God's dear Son.</P>
<P><PB N="177" REF="005311_0184_10181A8A03BBEEC0">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ay generally&mdash;For as God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> &s;acred Spirit <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">loweth not only on <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, but when &amp; how it li&s;teth&punc; Therefore, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">om me to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e fine <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Almighty to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Way of acting, or &s;ay, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">gree o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Conviction&mdash;No&punc; there is a holy <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">riety in God's Methods of calling home his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;But this we may affirm a&s;&s;uredly, <Q>that wherever there is a Work of true Conviction and Conver&s;ion wro't upon a Sinner's Heart, the Holy Gho&s;t, whether by a greater or le&s;s Degree of inward Soul-Trouble, does that which our Lord Je&s;us tells the Di&s;ciples in the Words of the Text, that he &s;hould do when he came.</Q></P>
<P>If any of you here ridicule inward Religion&punc; or think there's no &s;uch Thing as our feeling or receiving the Holy Gho&s;t, I fear my Preaching will be quite Fooli&s;hne&s;s to you, and that you will under&s;tand me no more, than if I &s;poke to you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> an unknown Tongue&mdash;But as the Pro|mi&s;e in the Text is made to the World, and as I know it will be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> till Time &s;hall be no <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, I &s;hall proceed to explain the general Way, whereby the Holy Gho&s;t works upon every con|verted Sinner's Heart&punc; and I hope that the Lord, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> whil&s;t I am &s;peaking, may be plea&s;ed to ful|fil it in many of your Hearts&mdash;<HI>And when he is come, he will reprove the World of Sin, of Righte|ou&s;ne&s;s, and of Judgment.</HI></P>
<P>The Word which we tran&s;late <HI>reprove,</HI> ought to be render'd <HI>convin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">,</HI> and in the Original it implies a <HI>Conviction</HI> by way of Argumentation&punc;
<PB N="178" REF="005311_0185_10181A8DDF029558">
and coming with a Power upon the Mind equal to a Demon&s;tration&mdash;A great many Scoffers o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> the&s;e la&s;t Days, will a&s;k &s;uch as they term <HI>Pre|te<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ders</HI> to the Spirit, how they feel the Spirit, and how they know the Spirit? They might as well a&s;k, how they know, and how they feel the Sun when it &s;hines upon the Body? For with equal Power and Demon&s;tration does the Spirit of God work upon and convince the Soul.</P>
<P>And <HI>Fir&s;t,</HI> It convinces of Sin&mdash;And gene|rally of &s;ome enormous Sin, the wor&s;t perhaps the convicted Per&s;on ever was guilty of&mdash;Thus when our Lord was conver&s;ing with the Woman of <HI>Samaria,</HI> he convinced her fir&s;t of her Adul|tery, <Q><HI>Woman,</HI> &s;ays he, <HI>Go call thy Hu&s;band&mdash;The Woman an&s;wered, and &s;aid, I have <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Hu&s;band&mdash;Je&s;us &s;aid unto her, Thou ha&s;t we<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> &s;aid, I have no Hu&s;band: For thou ha&s;t had five Hu&s;bands, and he whom thou now ha&s;t, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> not thy Hu&s;band: In this &s;aid&s;t thou truly.</HI></Q>&mdash;With this there went &s;uch a powerful Conviction of all her other actual Sins, that &s;oon after &s;he <HI>left her Water-pot, and went her Way into the City, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">aith to the Men, Come, and &s;ee a Man that told me all Things that ever I did: Is not this the Chri&s;t?</HI> Thus our Lord al&s;o dealt with the Per&s;ecutor <HI>Saul</HI>&mdash;He convinced him fir&s;t of the horrid Sin of Per&s;ecution&mdash;<HI>Saul, Saul, Why per&s;ecute&s;t thou N<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">?</HI> Such a Sen&s;e of all his other Sins, in all Probability, at the &s;ame Time revived in his Mind, that immediately he died; that is&punc; died to all his fal&s;e Confidences, and was thrown into &s;uch an Agony of Soul, that he continued three
<PB N="179" REF="005311_0186_10181A8F6F6076B8">
Days, and neither did eat or drink.&mdash;This is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ne Method the Spirit of God generally takes in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">aling with Sinners&mdash;He fir&s;t convinces them <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ome heinous actual Sin, and at the &s;ame time <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">rings all their other Sins into Remembrance, and as it were &s;ets them in Battle Array before them: <HI>When he is come, he will reprove the World <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Sin.</HI></P>
<P>And was it ever thus with you, my dear <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">earers? (For I mu&s;t que&s;tion you as I go along, becau&s;e I intend, by the divine Help, to preach not only to your Heads, but your Hearts)&mdash;Did the Spirit of God ever bring all your Sins thus&punc; to Remembrance, &amp; make you cry out to God, <HI>Thou write&s;t bitter Things again&s;t me?</HI> Did your actual Sins ever appear before you, as tho' drawn <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a Map? If not, you have great Rea&s;on (un|le&s;s you were &s;anctified from the Womb) to &s;u&s;|pect that you are not convicted, much more not converted, and that the Promi&s;e of the Text was never yet fulfilled in your Hearts.</P>
<P>Further: When the Comforter comes into a Sinner's Heart, tho' it generally convinces the Sinner of his <HI>actual</HI> Sin fir&s;t, yet it leads him to &s;ee and bewail his <HI>original</HI> Sin, the Fountain from which all the&s;e polluted Streams flow.</P>
<P>Tho' every Thing in Earth, Air, and Water, every Thing both without and within, concur to prove the Truth of that A&s;&s;ertion in the Scripture, <HI>viz.</HI> that <HI>in Adam we all have died;</HI> not mo&s;t are &s;o harden'd, thro' the Deceitfulne&s;s <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Sin, that notwith&s;tanding they may give an <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ent to the Truth of that Propo&s;ition in their
<PB N="180" REF="005311_0187_10181A910BD51D20">
Heads, yet they never felt it really in their Heart&mdash;Nay, &s;ome in Words profe&s;&s;edly deny it, th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> their Works, too, too plainly prove them to be degenerate Sons of a degenerate Father&mdash;But when the Comforter, the Spirit of God arre&s;ts a Sinner, and convinces him of Sin, all carnal Rea&s;oning again&s;t original Corruption, every proud and high Imagination, which exalteth it|&s;elf again&s;t that Doctrine, is immediately thrown down&mdash;And is made to cry out, <HI>Who &s;hall deli|ver me from the Body of this Death?</HI> He now finds that Concupi&s;cence is Sin&mdash;And does not &s;o much bewail his actual Sins, as the inward Perver&s;ene&s;s of his Heart, which he now finds not only to be an Enemy to, but al&s;o direct Enmity again&s;t God.</P>
<P>And did the Comforter, my dear Friends, ever come with &s;uch a convincing Power as this into your Hearts? Were you ever made to &s;ee and feel, that in your Fle&s;h dwelleth no good Thing&punc;&mdash;That you are conceived &amp; born in Sin&mdash;That you are by Nature Children of Wrath&mdash;That God would be ju&s;t if he damned you, tho' you never committed an actual Sin in your Lives? So often as you have been at Church and Sacra|ment, did you ever feelingly confe&s;s, that there was no Health in you&mdash;That the Remembrance of your original and actual Sins was <HI>grievous</HI> unto you, and the Burthen of them <HI>intolerable?</HI> If not, you have been only offering God vai<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> Ob|lations&mdash;You never yet prayed in your Lives&mdash;The Comfort never yet came effectually into your Souls&mdash;Con&s;equently you are not in the
<PB N="181" REF="005311_0188_10181A94354FB868">
Faith properly &s;o called&mdash;No, you are at pre&s;ent <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a State of Death and Damnation.</P>
<P><HI>Thirdly,</HI> The Comforter, when he comes effectually to work upon a Sinner, not only con|vinces him of the Sin of his Nature, the Sin of his Life, but al&s;o the Sin of his <HI>Duties.</HI></P>
<P>We all naturally are Legali&s;ts, thinking to be ju&s;tified by the Works of the Law&mdash;When &s;omewhat awakened by the Terrors of the Lord, we immediately, like the <HI>Phari&s;ees</HI> of old, go <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">bout to e&s;tabli&s;h our own Righteou&s;ne&s;s, and think we &s;hall find Acceptance with God, if we &s;eek it with Tears&mdash;Finding our&s;elves dam|ned by Nature, and our actual Sins, we the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> think to recommend our&s;elves to God by our Duties, and hope by our Doings of one Kind or another, to inherit eternal Life&mdash;But whenever the Comforter comes into the Heart, it con|vinces the Soul of the&s;e fal&s;e Re&s;ts, and makes the Sinner, to &s;ee that all his Righteou&s;ne&s;&s;es are but as filthy Rags&mdash;And that his be&s;t Works are but &s;o many &s;plendid Sins&mdash;And that for the mo&s;t pompous Services, he de&s;erves no bet|ter a Doom than that of the unprofitable Ser|vant, <HI>viz.</HI> to be thrown into outer Darkne&s;s, where is weeping, and wailing, and gna&s;hing of Teeth.</P>
<P>And was this Degree of Conviction ever wrought in any of your Souls? Did the Com|forter ever come into your Hearts, &s;o as to make you &s;ick of your Duties, as well as your Sins? Were you ever, with the <HI>Great Apo&s;tle</HI> of the <HI>Gentiles,</HI> made to abhor your own Righteou&s;|ne&s;s,
<PB N="182" REF="005311_0189_10181A974EB774C0">
which is by the Law, and acknowledge that you de&s;erve to be damned, tho' you &s;hould give all your Goods to feed the Poor? Were you made to feel that your very Repentance needed to be repented of, and that every Thing in your|&s;elves is but D<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ng and Dro&s;s?&mdash;And that all the Arguments you can retch for Mercy mu&s;t be out of the Heart, and pure unmerited Love o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> God? Were you ever made to lie at the Fee<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> of &s;overeign Grace, and to &s;ay, <Q>Lord, if thou wilt, thou may'&s;t &s;ave me, if not, thou may'&s;t ju&s;tly damn me&mdash;I have nothing to plead, I can in no wi&s;e ju&s;tify my &s;elf in thy Sight&mdash;My be&s;t Performances I &s;ee will condemn me.&mdash;And all I have to depend upon is thy free Grace</Q>&mdash;What &s;ay you? Was this eve<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">, or is this now, the habitual Language of your Hearts? You have been frequently at the Tem|ple. But did you ever approach it in th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Tem|ple<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> of the poor <HI>Publican;</HI> and after you have done all, acknowledge that you have done no|thing&mdash;And upon a feeling experimental Sen&s;e of your own Unworthine&s;s&punc; and Sinfulne&s;s, every way &s;mite upon your Brea&s;ts, and &s;ay, <HI>God be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, to us Sinners&punc;</HI> If you never were thus <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, the Comforter never yet effectually <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> into your Souls&mdash;You are out of Chri&s;t, and if God &s;hould require your Souls in that Con|dition, he would be no better to you than a con|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ming Fire.</P>
<P>But there is a <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Sin,</HI> which the Comfor|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters">, when he comes, convinces the Soul of, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> alone (it is very remarkable) but Lord
<PB N="183" REF="005311_0190_10181A9B649AC9E0">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> was the only Sin worth <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> it is the Root of all <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> It is the reigning, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Sin of the World&mdash;And what <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> that Sin may be?&mdash;It is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> that Root of all other Evils, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the Sin of <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;Of Sin,</HI> &s;ays our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">. Ver. <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>becau&s;e they believed not on me.</HI></P>
<P>But <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, the Chri&s;tian World, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> that hear me this Day, want <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Gho&s;t <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> convince you of Unbelief? <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> any Infidels here? Yes, (Oh! that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> not too great Rea&s;on to think &s;o) I fear m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;t are &s;uch&mdash;Not indeed &s;uch Infidels as pro|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">edly deny the Lord that bought us (tho' <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> fear too many even of &s;uch Mon&s;ters are in every Country;) but I mean &s;uch Unbelievers that have no more Faith in Chri&s;t than the Devils them&s;elves&mdash;Perhaps you may think you believe, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> you repeat the Creed, or &s;ub&s;cribe to a Confe&s;&s;ion of Faith&mdash;Becau&s;e you go to Church <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Meeting, receive the Sacrament, and are taken <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> full Communion&mdash;The&s;e are ble&s;&s;ed Pri|viledges, but all this may be done, without our <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> true Believers&mdash;And I know not how to detect your fal&s;e hypocritical Faith better, than <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> putting to you this Que&s;tion&mdash;Suppo&s;e I was to a&s;k you, "How long have you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">lieved?"&mdash;Would not mo&s;t of you &s;ay, <Q>As <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> we can remember, we never did <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">believe</Q>&mdash;Then this is a certain Sign that you have no true Faith at all&mdash;No, not &s;o much as a Grain of M<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;tard Seed&mdash;For if you believe now, (unle&s;s you were
<PB N="184" REF="005311_0191_10181A9F021975D8">
&s;anctified in your Infancy) you mu&s;t know that there was a Time, in which you did not believe on the Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t&mdash;And the Holy Gho&s;t, if ever you received it, convinced you of this&mdash;Eternal Truth has declared, <HI>when he is come, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e will convince the World of Sin, becau&s;e they be|lieve not on me.</HI></P>
<P>None of us believe by Nature&mdash;But after the Holy Gho&s;t has convinced us of the Sin of our Natures, and the Sin of our Lives, and Duties, in order to convince us of our utter Inability to &s;ave our&s;elves, and that we mu&s;t be beholden to God, as for every thing el&s;e, &s;o for Faith (with|out which, it is impo&s;&s;ible to plea&s;e, or be &s;aved <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">y Chri&s;t.) He convinces us al&s;o, that we have no Faith&mdash;Do&s;t thou believe on the Son of God? is the grand Que&s;tion which the Holy Gho&s;t now puts to the Soul&mdash;At the &s;ame Time he works with &s;uch Power and Demon&s;tration, that the Soul &s;ees, and is obliged to confe&s;s that it has no Faith.</P>
<P>This is a Thing little thought of by mo&s;t that call them&s;elves Believers&mdash;They dream they are Chri&s;tians, becau&s;e they live in a Chri&s;tian Country&mdash;If they were born <HI>Turks,</HI> they would believe on <HI>Mahomet</HI>&mdash;For what is that which Men commonly call Faith, but an outward Con|&s;ent to the e&s;tabli&s;h'd Religion? But do not you thus deceive your own &s;elves&mdash;For true Faith is quite another Thing&mdash;A&s;k your &s;elves therefore, whether or not the Holy Gho&s;t ever powerfully convinced you of the Sin of Unbe|lief? You are perhaps &s;o devout (as you may
<PB N="185" REF="005311_0192_10181AA28517D158">
imagine) as to get a Catalogue of Sins, which you look over, and confe&s;s in a formal Manner, as often as you go to the Holy Sacrament&mdash;But among&s;t all your Sins, did you ever once con|fe&s;s and bewail that damning Sin of <HI>Unbelief?</HI>&mdash;Were you ever made to cry out, <Q>Lord, give me Faith&mdash;Lord, give me to believe on thee, Oh, that I had Faith&punc;&mdash;Oh, that I could believe!</Q> If you never were thus di&s;tre&s;&s;ed&mdash;At lea&s;t, if you never &s;aw and felt, that you had no Faith, it is a certain Sign that the Holy Gho&s;t the Comforter, never came into, and worked, &s;avingly upon your Souls.</P>
<P>But is it not odd, that the Holy Gho&s;t &s;hould, be called a Comforter, when it is plain, by they Experience of all God's Children, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> of Conviction is u&s;ually attended with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Conflicts, and a great deal of Soul&punc;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">?&mdash;I an&s;wer, the Holy Gho&s;t may well <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> termed a Comforter, even in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Work&mdash;Be|cau&s;e it is the only Way to, and ends in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Comfort&mdash;Ble&s;&s;ed are they that are th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> convicted by him, for they &s;hall be comforted Nay, not only &s;o, but there is pre&s;ent Comfort&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> in the mid&s;t of the&s;e Convictions&mdash;The <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> rejoice in the Sight of its own Mi&s;ery&mdash;Ble&s;&s;es God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> bringing <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Darkne&s;s into Light, and looks forward with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Comfortable Pro&s;pect of fu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">re Deliverance<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> knowing, that tho' Sorrow <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ay endure for a Night, Joy will come in the Morning.</P>
<P>Thus it is that the Holy Gho&s;t convinces the Soul of Sin&mdash;And if &s;o, holy wretchedly <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;
<PB N="186" REF="005311_0193_10181AA55E4F7DB0">
they mi&s;taken, that blind the Light of the Spirit with the Light of Con&s;cience, as all &s;uch do, who &s;ay, <Q>that Chri&s;t lighteth every Man that cometh into the World, and that Light, if improved, will bring us to Je&s;us Chri&s;t.</Q>&mdash;If &s;uch Doctrine be true, the Promi&s;e in the Text was needle&s;s&mdash;Our Lord's Apo&s;tles had already that Light&mdash;The World hereafter to be con|vinced had that Light&mdash;And if that was &s;uffici|ent to bring them to Chri&s;t, why was it expedi|ent that Chri&s;t &s;hould go away to Heaven, to &s;end down the Holy Gho&s;t to do this for them&mdash;Alas! all have not this Spirit&mdash;It is the &s;pe|cial Gift of God, and without this &s;pecial Gift, we can never come to Chri&s;t.</P>
<P>The <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> of Con&s;cience will accu&s;e or con|vince us of any common Sin&mdash;But the Light of natural Con&s;cience never did, never will, and never can convince of Unbelief&mdash;If it could, how comes it to pa&s;s, that not one of the Hea|thens, who improved the Light of Nature in &s;uch an eminent Degree, was ever convinced of Unbelief? No, natural Con&s;cience cannot effect this&mdash;It is the peculiar Property of the Holy Gho&s;t the Comforter&mdash;<HI>When he is come, he will reprove</HI> (or convince) <HI>the World of Sin, of Righteou&s;ne&s;s, and Judgment.</HI></P>
<P>We have heard how he convince of Sin&mdash;We come now to &s;hew, what is the <HI>Righteou&s;|ne&s;s</HI> which the Comforter convinces the World of.</P>
<P>By the Word <HI>Righteou&s;ne&s;s,</HI> in &s;ome Places of Scripture, we are to under&s;tand that common
<PB N="187" REF="005311_0194_10181AA81875F680">
Ju&s;tice which we ought to practi&s;e between Man and Man&mdash;As when <HI>Paul</HI> is &s;aid to rea&s;on of <HI>Temperance</HI> and <HI>Righteou&s;ne&s;s</HI> before a trembling <HI>Felix</HI>&mdash;But here (as in a Multitude of other Places in holy Writ) we are to under&s;tand by the Word <HI>Righteou&s;ne&s;s,</HI> the active and pa&s;&s;ive Obedience of the dear Lord Je&s;us&mdash;Even that perfect, per&s;onal, all-&s;ufficient Righteou&s;ne&s;s, which he has wrought out for that World which the Spirit is to convince&mdash;<HI>Of Righteou&s;ne&s;s,</HI> &s;ays our Lord, <HI>becau&s;e I go to the Father, and ye &s;ee me no more</HI>&mdash;This is one Argument that the Holy Spirit makes u&s;e of to prove Chri&s;t's Righteou&s;ne&s;s&mdash;Becau&s;e he is gone to the Father, and we &s;ee him no more&mdash;For, had he not wrought out a &s;ufficient Righteou&s;ne&s;s, the Father would have &s;ent him back, as not having done what he un|dertook, and we &s;hould have &s;een him again.</P>
<P>Oh, the Righteou&s;ne&s;s of Chri&s;t! It &s;o com|forts my Soul, that I mu&s;t be excu&s;ed if I men|tion it in all my Di&s;cour&s;es&mdash;I would not, if I could help it, have one Sermon without it&mdash;Whatever Infidels may object, or <HI>Arminians</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ophi&s;tically argue again&s;t an <HI>imputed Righteou&s;|ne&s;s</HI>&mdash;Yet whoever know them&s;elves and God, mu&s;t acknowledge, that Je&s;us Chri&s;t is the End of the Law for Righteou&s;ne&s;s, and perfect Ju&s;ti|fication, in the Sight of God, to every one that believeth. And that we are to be made th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Righteou&s;ne&s;s of God in him&mdash;This, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> only a poor Sinner can lay hold of, <HI>becau&s;e</HI> Anchor of his Hope&mdash;Whatever <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> that is, of Salvation Men may <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ay, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> hold on Chri&s;t's
<PB N="188" REF="005311_0195_10180E325FD283D0">
&s;ee no other Foundation whereon to build my Hopes of Salvation, but on the Rock of Chri&s;t's per&s;onal Righteou&s;ne&s;s imputed to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Soul.</P>
<P>Many I believe have a rational Conviction of, and agree with me in this&mdash;But rational Con|victions, if re&s;ted in, avail but little&mdash;It mu&s;t be a &s;piritual, experimental Conviction of the Truth which is &s;aving&mdash;And therefore our Lord &s;ays&mdash;When the Holy Gho&s;t comes, in the Day of his Power, it convinces of this Righteou&s;ne&s;s, <HI>viz.</HI> of the Reality, and Compleatne&s;s, &amp; Sufficiency of it, to &s;ave a poor Sinner.</P>
<P>In the foregoing Part of this Di&s;cour&s;e, we &s;hewed how the Holy Gho&s;t convinces the Sin|ner of the Sin of his Nature, Life, Duties, an<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> of the Sin of Unbelief&mdash;And what then mu&s;t the poor Creature do? He mu&s;t, he mu&s;t inevi|tably de&s;pair, if there be no Hope but <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">n him|&s;elf&mdash;When therefore the Spirit has haunted the Sinner out of all his fal&s;e Re&s;ts &amp; Hiding-Places, taken off the pitiful Fig-leaves of his own Work<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> and driven him out of the Trees of the Garden (his outward Reformations) and placed him naked before the Bar of a &s;overeign, holy, ju&s;t, and Sin-avenging God; then, then it is, when the Soul, having the Sentence of Death within it&s;elf becau&s;e of Unbelief, has a &s;weet Di&s;play <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Chri&s;t's Righteou&s;ne&s;s made to it by the Holy Spirit of God&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> is that he begins <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> We <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to act in the Quality of a Comforter, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the Soul &s;o powerfully of the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> All-&s;ufficiency of Chri&s;t's <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"></P>
<P>By the Word&punc; Soul <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> immediately &s;et a <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Scripture, we are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">
<PB N="189" REF="005311_0196_10181AAB679C26E8">
and thir&s;ting after it&mdash;Now the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> begins to &s;ee&punc; that tho' he ha&s;t de&s;troyed him&s;elf, yet in Chri&s;t is his Help&mdash;That tho' he has no Righteou&s;ne&s;s of his own to recommend him, there is a Fulne&s;s of Grace, a Fulne&s;s of Truth, a Fulne&s;s of Righteou&s;ne&s;s in the dear Lord Je&s;us, which, if once imputed to him, would make him happy for ever and ever.</P>
<P>None, none can tell, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> tho&s;e happy Souls who have experienced it&punc; with what Demon|&s;tration of the Spirit this Conviction comes&mdash;Oh, how amiable, as well as all-&s;ufficient, does the ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us now appear! With what new Eyes does the Soul now &s;ee the Lord its Righ|teou&s;ne&s;s! Brethren, it is unutterable&mdash;If you were never thus convinced of Chri&s;t's Righte|ou&s;ne&s;s in your own Souls, tho' you may believe at doctrinally, it will avail yo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> nothing&mdash;The Comforter never came &s;avingly into your Souls&mdash;And then you are comfortle&s;s indeed.</P>
<P>But what will this Righteou&s;ne&s;s avail, if the Soul has it not in Po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ion?&mdash;The next Thing therefore the Comforter, when he comes, con|vinces the Soul of, is <HI>Judgment.</HI></P>
<P>By the Word <HI>Judgment,</HI> I under&s;tand that well-grounded Peace, that &s;ettled Judgment, which the Soul forms of it&s;elf, when it is enabled by the Spirit of God, to lay hold on Chri&s;t's Righteou&s;ne&s;s, which I believe it always does, when convinced in the Manner before-mention|ed&mdash;<Q><HI>Of Judgment,</HI> &s;ays our Lord, <HI>becau&s;e the Prince of this World is judged;</HI></Q> that is, the Soul, being enabled to lay hold on Chri&s;t's
<PB N="190" REF="005311_0197_10181AB094E960D8">
perfect Righteou&s;ne&s;s <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a lively Faith, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> Conviction wrought in it by the Holy Spirit, that the <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> this World is now judged</HI>&mdash;The S<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">l, being now ju&s;tified by Faith, it has Peace with God, through our Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t, and can triumphantly &s;ay, <Q>It is Chri&s;t that ju&s;ti|fies me, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> now that condemns me? The &s;trong Man armed is now ca&s;t out&punc; My Soul is now in a true Peace&mdash;The <HI>Prince of this World</HI> will come and accu&s;e, but he ha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> now no Share in me&mdash;The Ble&s;&s;ed Spirit which I have received, and whereby I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> enabled to apply Chri&s;t's Righteou&s;ne&s;s to my poor Soul, powerfully convinces me of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Why &s;hould I fear? Or o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> what &s;hall I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words">, &s;ince God's Spirit witne&s;&s;es with my Spirit, that I am a Child of God? The Lord <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> up on High&mdash;He has <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ed Captivity Captive&mdash;He has received the Holy Gho&s;t the Comforter, that be&s;t of Gifts for Men, and that Comforter is come into my Heart&mdash;He is faithful that hath promi&s;ed&mdash;I, even I, am powerfully, rationally, &s;piritually convi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">d of <HI>Sin, Righteou&s;ne&s;s and Judgment</HI>&mdash;By this I know the <HI>Prince of this World is judged.</HI></Q></P>
<P>Thus, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, may we &s;uppo&s;e the Soul to tri|umph, in which the Promi&s;e of the Text is hap|pily fulfilled&mdash;And tho' at the Beginning of this <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> &s;aid m<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;t had never experienced any thing of this, and that therefore this Preaching mu&s;t be Fooli&s;hne&s;s to mo&s;t, yet I doubt not but there are &s;ome few happy Souls, who, thro' Grace, have been enabled to follow me Step by
<PB N="191" REF="005311_0198_10181AB625265C58">
Step&mdash;And notwith&s;tanding the Holy Gho&s;t might at directly work in the &s;ame Order a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> I have <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e&s;cribed, and perhaps they cannot exactly &s;ay <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Time when, yet they have a well-grounded confidence that the Work is done, and that they we really been convinced of <HI>Sin, Righteou&s;ne&s;s and Judgment,</HI> in &s;ome Way, or at &s;ome Time <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> another.</P>
<P>And now, what &s;hall I &s;ay to you? O thank God, thank the Lord Je&s;us, thank the ever-<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">le&s;&s;ed Trinity, for this un&s;peakable Gift&mdash;For you would never have been thus highly favoured, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> not he, who fir&s;t &s;poke Darkne&s;s into Light, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ved you with an everla&s;ting Love, and enligh|ten'd you by his Holy Spirit, and that too, not&punc;</P>
<P>Account of any good Thing fore&s;een in you, but for his own Name's Sake.</P>
<P>Be humble therefore, O Believers, be humble&mdash;Look to the Rock from whence you have been <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ewn&mdash;Extol <HI>Free Grace</HI>&mdash;Admire <HI>Electing Love,</HI> which alone has made you to differ from the re&s;t of your Brethren&mdash;Has God bro't you into Light? Walk as becom<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">h Children of Light&mdash;Provoke not the Holy Spirit to depart from you&mdash;For tho' he hath &s;ealed you to the Day of Redemption, and you know that the <HI>Prince of this World is judged;</HI> yet if you back&s;lide, grow lukewarm, or forget your fir&s;t Love, the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> will vi&s;it your Offences with the Rod of Affliction, and your Sin with &s;piritual Scourges&mdash;Be not therefore high-minded, but fear&mdash;Rejoice, but let it be with Trembling&mdash;As the Elect of God, put on not only Humblene&s;s of Mind, but
<PB N="192" REF="005311_0199_10181AB8A568A518">
Bowels of Compa&s;&s;ion, and pray, Oh pray, for your unconverted Brethren!&mdash;Help me, help me now, O Children of God, and hold up <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">y Hands, as <HI>Aaron</HI> and <HI>Hur</HI> once held up the Hands of <HI>Mo&s;es</HI>&mdash;Pray, whil&s;t I am Preaching, that the Lord may enable me to &s;ay, <Q>This Day is the Promi&s;e in the Text fulfilled in &s;ome poor Sinners Hearts</Q>&mdash;Cry mightily to God, and with the Cords of a holy Violence, pull down Ble&s;&s;ings on your Neighbours Heads&mdash;Chri&s;t yet lives and reigns in Heaven&mdash;The Re&s;idue of the Spirit is yet in his Hand, and a plentiful Effu&s;ion of it is promi&s;ed in the latter Days of the Church&mdash;And Oh that the Holy Gho&s;t, the ble&s;&s;ed Comforter, would now come down, and convince tho&s;e that are Chri&s;tle&s;s among&s;t you, <HI>of Sin, of Righteou&s;ne&s;s, &amp; of Judg|ment!</HI> Oh that you were once made willing to be convinced!&mdash;But perhaps you had rather be filled with Wine, than with the Spirit, and are daily cha&s;ing that Holy Gue&s;t from your Souls&mdash;What &s;hall I &s;ay for you to God? <Q><HI>Father for|give them, for they know not what they do?</HI></Q> What &s;hall I &s;ay from God to you?&mdash;Why? that God was in Chri&s;t reconciling the World unto him&s;elf&mdash;Therefore I be&s;eech you, as in Chri&s;t's Stead, be ye reconciled to God&mdash;Do not go away contradicting and bla&s;pheming&mdash;I know Satan would have you be gone&mdash;Many of you may be unea&s;y, and are ready to cry <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ut&punc; <HI>What a Wearine&s;s is this!</HI> But I will not let you go&mdash;I have wre&s;tled with God for my Hearers in private, and I mu&s;t wre&s;tle with you
<PB N="193" REF="005311_0200_10181B29DCBB4538">
<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> publick&mdash;Tho' of my&s;elf I can do no <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, and you can no more by your own Powe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to, and believe on Chri&s;t, than <HI>Lazaru<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> come forth from the Grave, yet who <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> but God may beget &s;ome of you again <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Hope by this Fooli&s;hne&s;s of Preaching, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> that you may be &s;ome of that World, which th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Comforter is to convince <HI>of Sin, of Righte|ou&s;ne&s;s, and of Judgment?</HI>&mdash;Poor, Chri&s;tle&s;s <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> do you know what a Condition you are <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Why you are lying in the wicked One, the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;He is in you&mdash;He rules in you, he walks <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> in you, unle&s;s you dwell in Chri&s;t, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the Comforter is come into your Hearts&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> contentedly lie in that wicked <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the Devil? What Wages will he give <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Eternal Death&mdash;Oh that you would <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to Chri&s;t!&mdash;The Free Gift of God thro <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> is eternal Life&mdash;He will accept of you even <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&punc; if you will believe in him&mdash;The Comforter <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ay yet come into your Hearts, even yours&mdash;All that are now his living Temples, were once <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ing in the wicked One, as well as you&mdash;This ble&s;&s;ed Gift, this Holy Gho&s;t, the ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us received even for the Rebellious&mdash;Oh that he would &s;hew me that he has received it for &s;ome of you!&mdash;I &s;ee many of you affected&mdash;But are your Pa&s;&s;ions only a little wrought upon, or are your Souls really touched with a lively Sen&s;e of the Heinou&s;ne&s;s of your Sins, your Want of Faith, or the Preciou&s;ne&s;s of the Righteou&s;ne&s;s of Je&s;us Chri&s;t? If &s;o, I hope the Lord has been graci|ous, &amp; the Comforter is coming into your Hearts.
<PB N="194" REF="005311_0201_10181B2B6BA4DDE8">
O do not &s;tifle the&s;e Convictions!&mdash;Do not go away, and &s;trait way forget what Manner of Doc|trine you have heard, and thereby &s;hew, that the&s;e are only common Workings of a few tran&s;i|ent Convictions, floating upon the Surface of your Hearts&mdash;Beg of God that you may be &s;incere (for he alone can make you &s;o) and that you may in|deed de&s;ire that the Promi&s;e of the Text may be fulfilled in your Souls&mdash;Who knows but the Lord may be gracious? Remember you have no Plea but &s;overeign Mercy&mdash;But for your Encourage|ment al&s;o, remember it is the World, &s;uch as you are, to whom the Comforter is to come, and whom he is to convince&mdash;Wait therefore at Wi&s;|dom's Gates&mdash;The bare Probability of having a Door of Mercy open'd, is enough to keep you <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">&mdash;Chri&s;t Je&s;us came into the World to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e Sinner, the Chief of them&mdash;You know not but he came to &s;ave you&mdash;Do not go and quarrel with God's Decrees, and &s;ay, if I am a Repro|bate, I &s;hall be damned; if I am elected, I &s;hall be &s;aved, and therefore I'll do nothing&mdash;What have you to do with God's Decrees? Secret Things belong to him&mdash;It is your Bu&s;ine&s;s to add all Diligence to make your Calling and Elec|tion &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">re&mdash;I<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> there are but few that find the Way that leads to Life, do you &s;trive to be &s;ome of them&mdash;You know not but you may be in the Number of tho&s;e few, and that your &s;triving may be the Means which God intends to ble&s;s, to give you an Entrance in&mdash;If you do not act thus, you are un&s;incere&mdash;And if you do, who knows but you may find Mercy? For though,
<PB N="195" REF="005311_0202_10181B2E20D07F58">
after you have done all that you can, God may ju&s;tly cut you off, yet never was a &s;ingle Per&s;on damned that did all that he could&mdash;Tho' there|fore your Hands are withered, &s;tretch them out&mdash;Tho' you are impotent, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ck and lame, come lie at the Pool&mdash;Who knows, but by and by the Lord Je&s;us may have Compa&s;&s;ion on you, and &s;end the Comforter to convince you of <HI>Sin, Righteou&s;ne&s;s,</HI> and <HI>of Judgment?</HI> He is a God full of Com|pa&s;&s;ion and Long-&s;uffering, otherwi&s;e you and I had been long &s;ince lifting up our Eyes in Tor|ments&mdash;But &s;till he is patient with us&mdash;Yet, O Chri&s;tle&s;s Sinners, you are alive, and who knows but God intends to bring you to Repentance? Could my Prayers or Tears effect it, you &s;hould have Vollies of the one, and Floods of the other&mdash;My Heart is now touched with a Sen&s;e of your Condition&mdash;May our merciful High-Prie&s;t now &s;end down the Comforter, and make you &s;en&s;i|ble of it al&s;o!&mdash;Oh the Love of Chri&s;t! <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> con|&s;trains me yet to be&s;eech you to come to him&mdash;Oh what do you reject, if you reject Chri&s;t, the <HI>Lord of Glory!</HI>&mdash;Oh, Sinners, give the dear Redeemer a Lodging in your Souls&mdash;Do not be <HI>Bethlemites</HI>&mdash;Sons and Daughters give Chri&s;t your Hearts, your whole Hearts&mdash;Indeed he is wor|thy&mdash;He made you, and not you your&s;elves&mdash;You are not your own&mdash;Oh give Chri&s;t then your Bodies and Souls, which are his!&mdash;Is it not enough to melt you down, to think that the high and lofty One, that inhabiteth Eternity, &s;hould <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> conde&s;cend to invite you by his Mini&s;ter? How &s;oon can he frown you to Hell? And
<PB N="196" REF="005311_0203_10181B2FBA134F40">
how know you, but he may <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> In&s;tant, if you do not hear his Voice?&mdash;Did any yet harden their Hearts again&s;t Chri&s;t, and pro&s;per? Come then, do not &s;end me &s;orrowful away! Do not let me have Rea&s;on to cry out, <Q>O my Lean|ne&s;s, my Leanne&s;s!</Q>&mdash;Do not let me go weeping into my Clo&s;et, and &s;ay, <Q>Lord, they will not believe my Report&mdash;Lord, I have called them, and they will not an&s;wer, I am unto them as a very plea&s;ant Song, and as one that plays upon a plea&s;ant In&s;trument; but their Hearts are running after the Lu&s;t of the Eye, the Lu&s;t of the Fle&s;h, and the Pride of Life</Q>&mdash;Would you be willing that I &s;hould give &s;uch an Account of you, or make &s;uch a Prayer before God? And yet I mu&s;t not only do &s;o here, but appear in Judgment again&s;t you hereafter, unle&s;s you will come to Chri&s;t&mdash;Once more therefore I intreat you to come&mdash;What Objections have you to make?&mdash;Behold <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;tand here in the Name of God, to an&s;wer all that you can offer&mdash;But I know no one can come, unle&s;s the Father draw him&mdash;I will there|fore addre&s;s me to my God, and intercede with him to &s;end the Comforter into your Hearts.</P>
<P><Q>O ble&s;&s;ed Je&s;us, who art a God who&s;e Compa&s;&s;ions fail not, and in whom all the Promi&s;es are <HI>Yea</HI> and <HI>Amen;</HI> thou that fitte&s;t between the Cherubims, &s;hew thy&s;elf among&s;t&punc; us&mdash;Oh let us now &s;ee thy Outgoings!&mdash;Oh let us now ta&s;te that thou art gracious, and reveal thy Almighty Arm!&mdash;Get thy&s;elf the Victory in the&s;e poor Sinners Hearts&mdash;Let
<PB N="197" REF="005311_0204_10181B31B0F923D0">
not the Word &s;poken, prove like Water &s;pilt upon the Ground&mdash;Send down, &s;end down, O great High-Prie&s;t, the Holy Spirit to con|vince the World of <HI>Sin,</HI> of <HI>Righteou&s;ne&s;s,</HI> and of <HI>Judgment</HI>&mdash;So will we give Thanks and Prai&s;e to thee for ever&mdash;Even to thee O Fa|ther, thee O Son, and thee O ble&s;&s;ed Spirit; to whom, as three Per&s;ons but one God, be a&s;cribed by Angels and Arch-Angels, by Cherubims and Seraphims, and all the hea|venly Ho&s;t, all po&s;&s;ible Power, Might, Ma|je&s;ty, and Dominion, now and for ever|more.</Q> <HI>Amen, Amen, Amen.</HI></P>
