<HI>Zaccheus</HI> thought within him&s;elf. But what &s;aith the Scripture? <HI>I will make a willing Peo|ple in the Day of my Power</HI>&mdash;With this outward Call, there went an efficacious Power from God, which &s;weetly over-ruled his natural Will; and therefore, Ver. 6. <HI> "He made ha&s;te, and came down, and received him joyfully"</HI>&mdash;Not only into his Hou&s;e, but al&s;o into his Heart.</P>
<P>Thus it is the great God brings home his Children. He calls them by Name, by his Word or Providence&mdash;He &s;peaks to them by his Spirit&mdash;Hereby they are enabled to open their Hearts, and are made willing to receive the King of Glory in&mdash;For <HI>Zaccheus'</HI>s &s;ake let us not intirely condemn People that come under the Word, out of no better Principle than <HI>Curio&s;ity.</HI> Who knows but God may call them? It is good to be where the Lord is pa&s;&s;ing by&mdash;<HI>May all that are now pre&s;ent, out of this Princi|ple, hear the Voice of the Son of God &s;peaking to their Souls, and &s;o hear that they may live!</HI> Not that Men ought therefore to take Encourage|ment to come out of Curio&s;ity&mdash;For perhaps a thou&s;and more, at other Times, came to &s;ee Chri&s;t out of Curio&s;ity, as well as well as <HI>Zac|cheus,</HI> which were not effectually called by hi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Grace&mdash;I only mention this for the Encourage|ment of my own Soul, and the Con&s;olation of God's Children, who are too apt to be angry with tho&s;e who do not attend on the Word out of Love to God&mdash;But let them alone&mdash;Brethren pray for them&mdash;How do you know but Je&s;us Chri&s;t may &s;peak to their Hearts? A few Word
