<P>Say not any of you within your&s;elves, this is a licentious, <HI>Antinomian</HI> Doctrine&mdash;For the Faith, if true, will work by Love, and be pro|ductive of the Fruits of Holine&s;s&mdash;See an In&s;ta<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> in this Convert <HI>Zaccheus</HI>&mdash;No &s;ooner had he re|ceived Je&s;us Chri&s;t by Faith into his Heart, but he evidences it by his Works&mdash;For, <HI>Ver.</HI> 8. we w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> are told, <Q><HI>Zaccheus &s;tood forth, and &s;aid unto the Lord, Behold, Lord, the half of my Goods I give unto the Poor; and if I have ta|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">en any thing from any Man by fal&s;e Accu&s;ation I re&s;tore him Four-fold.</HI></Q></P>
<P>Having believed on Je&s;us in his Heart, he now makes Confe&s;&s;ion of him with his Mouth to Salvation&mdash;<HI>Zaccheus &s;tood forth</HI>&mdash;He was not a&s;hamed, but <HI>&s;tood forth</HI> before his Brother <HI>Pub|licans</HI>&mdash;For true Faith ca&s;ts out all &s;ervile, &s;inful Fear of Man&mdash;<HI>"And &s;aid, Behold, Lord"</HI>&mdash;It is remarkable how readily People in Scripture have owned the Divinity of Chri&s;t immediately upon their Conver&s;ion&mdash;Thus the Woman at <HI>Jacob'</HI>s Well&mdash;<HI>"Is not this the Chri&s;t?"</HI> Thus the Man born blind&mdash;<HI>"Lord I believe, and wor&s;hipped him."</HI> Thus <HI>Zaccheus, "Behold, Lord."</HI> An inconte&s;table Proof this to me, that tho&s;e who deny our Lord's Divinity, never effectually felt his Power&mdash;If they had, they would not &s;peak &s;o lightly of him&mdash;They would &s;corn to deny his eternal Power and Godhead&mdash;<Q><HI>Zaccheus &s;tood
<PB N="211" REF="005311_0218_10181B5D2E779588">
forth, and &s;aid, Behold, Lord, the half of my Goods, I give to the Poor, and if I have taken any thing from any Man by fal&s;e Accu&s;ation, I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> him Four-fold.</HI></Q>&mdash;Oh noble Fruits of a true living Faith in the Lord Je&s;us!&mdash;Every Word calls for our Notice&mdash;Not &s;ome &s;mall, not the tenth Part, but the half&mdash;Of what? My <HI>Goods</HI>&mdash;Things that were valuable <HI>My</HI> Goods&mdash;His <HI>own</HI> not <HI>anothers</HI>&mdash;I <HI>give,</HI> not I <HI>will give</HI> when I die, when I can keep them no longer; but I give now, even now. <HI>Zaccheus</HI> would be his own Executor. <HI>For whil&s;t we have Time we &s;hould do good</HI>&mdash;But to whom would he give half of his Goods? Not to the Rich, not to tho&s;e who were already clothed in Purple and fine Linnen, of whom he might be recompen&s;ed again; but to the Poor, the Maimed, the Halt, the Blind, from which he could expect no Recompence till the Re&s;urrec|tion of the Dead&mdash;<HI>I give to the Poor</HI>&mdash;But know|ing that he mu&s;t be ju&s;t, before he could be charitable, and con&s;cious to him&s;elf, that in his publick Admini&s;trations he had wronged many Per&s;ons, he adds, <Q><HI>And if I have taken any thing from any Man by fal&s;e Accu&s;ation, I re&s;tore him Four-fold</HI></Q>&mdash;Hear ye this, all ye that make no Con&s;cience of cheating the King of his Taxes, or of buying or rolling Run Goods&mdash;If ever God gives you true Faith, you will never re&s;t, till, like <HI>Zaccheus,</HI> you have made Re&s;titu|tion to the utmo&s;t of your Power&mdash;I &s;uppo&s;e before his Conver&s;ion, he thought it no Harm<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> to cheat thus, no more than you may do now,
<PB N="212" REF="005311_0219_10181B5F0058CA78">
and plea&s;ed him&s;elf frequently to be &s;ure, that he got &s;o rich by doing &s;o&mdash;But now he is grieved for it at his Heart&mdash;He confe&s;&s;es his Inju&s;tice before Men, and promi&s;es to make ample Re&s;titution&mdash;Go ye cheating <HI>Publicans,</HI> learn of <HI>Zaccheus</HI>&mdash;Go away and do likewi&s;e. If you do not make Re&s;titution here, the Lord Je&s;us &s;hall make you confe&s;s it before Men and Angels, and condemn you for it when he comes in the Glory of his Father to Judgment here|after.</P>
<P>After all this, with good Rea&s;on might our Lord &s;ay unto him&mdash;<Q><HI>This Day is Salvation come to this Hou&s;e&mdash;For &s;omuch as he al&s;o is the Son of Abraham</HI></Q>&mdash;Not &s;o much by a natural, as by a &s;piritual Birth. He was made Partaker of like precious Faith with <HI>Abraham</HI>&mdash;Like <HI>Abraham</HI> he believed on the Lord, and it was accounted to him for Righteou&s;ne&s;s&mdash;His Faith, like <HI>Abraham'</HI>s, worked by Love, and I doubt not, but he has been long &s;ince &s;itting in <HI>Abra|ham'</HI>s Harbour.</P>
<P>And now are you not a&s;hamed of your&s;elves, who &s;peak again&s;t the Doctrines of Grace, e&s;pe|cially that Doctrine of being ju&s;tified by Faith alone, as tho' it leaded to Licentiou&s;ne&s;s? What can be more unju&s;t than &s;uch a Charge? Is not the In&s;tance of <HI>Zaccheus</HI> a &s;ufficient Proof to the contrary? Have I &s;trained it to &s;erve my own Turn? God forbid&mdash;To the be&s;t of my Knowledge I have &s;poken the Truth in Sincerity and the Truth as it is in Je&s;us&mdash;I do affirm that we are &s;aved <HI>by Grace,</HI> and that we are ju&s;tified
<PB N="213" REF="005311_0220_10181B6091528A30">
<HI>by Faith alone</HI>&mdash;But I do al&s;o affirm, that Faith mu&s;t be evidenced by Good Works, where there <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> an Opportunity of performing them.</P>
<P>What therefore has been &s;aid of <HI>Zaccheus,</HI> may &s;erve as a Rule, whereby all may judge whether they have Faith or not&mdash;You &s;ay you have Faith&mdash;But how do you prove it? Did you ever hear the Lord Je&s;us call you by Name? Were you ever made to obey that Call? Did you ever, like <HI>Zaccheus,</HI> receive Je&s;us Chri&s;t joyfully into your Hearts? Are you influenced by the Faith you &s;ay you have, to &s;tand up and conte&s;s the Lord Je&s;us before Men? Were you ever made willing to own, and humble your &s;elves for your pa&s;t Offences? Does your Faith work by Love, &s;o that you con&s;cientiou&s;ly lay up, according as God as pro&s;pered you, for the Support of the Poor? Do you give Alms of all Things that you po&s;&s;e&s;s? And have you made due Re&s;titution to tho&s;e you have wronged? If &s;o, happy are ye&mdash;Salvation is come to your Souls&mdash;You are Sons, you are Daughters of, you &s;hall &s;hortly be everla&s;tingly ble&s;&s;ed with, faithful <HI>Abraham.</HI> But if you are not thus minded, do not deceive your own Souls&mdash;Tho' you may talk of Ju&s;tification by Faith like Angels, it will do you no Good&mdash;It will only increa&s;e your Damnation&mdash;You hold the Truth, but it is in Unrighteou&s;ne&s;s. Your Faith, being without Works, is dead&mdash;You have the <HI>Devil,</HI> not <HI>Abraham,</HI> for your Father&mdash;Unle&s;s you get a Faith of the Heart, a Faith working by Love, with Devils and damned Spirits &s;hall you dwell for evermore.</P>
<P><PB N="214" REF="005311_0221_10181B65E4974770">
But it is Time now to enforce the latter Part of the Text&mdash;<HI>"For the Son of Man is come to &s;eek and to &s;ave that which was lo&s;t"</HI>&mdash;The&s;e Words are &s;poken by our Saviour in An&s;wer to &s;ome &s;elf-righteous <HI>Phari&s;ees,</HI> who, in&s;tead of rejoycing with the Angels in Heaven at the Con|ver&s;ion of &s;uch a Sinner, murmured, &s;aying, <HI>that he was gone to be a Gue&s;t with a Man that was a Sinner</HI>&mdash;To vindicate his Conduct, he tells them, that this was an Act agreeable to the De&s;ign of his Coming&mdash;<HI>For the Son of Man is come to &s;eek and to &s;ave that which was lo&s;t</HI>&mdash;He might have &s;aid the <HI>Son of God</HI>&mdash;But Oh the wonderful Conde&s;cen&s;ion of our Redeemer! He delights to &s;tile him&s;elf the <HI>Son of Man</HI>&mdash;He came, &s;ays he, not only to &s;ave, <HI>but to &s;eek and to &s;ave that which was lo&s;t</HI>&mdash;He came to <HI>Jericho</HI> to &s;eek and &s;ave <HI>Zaccheus.</HI> For other|wi&s;e <HI>Zaccheus</HI> would never have been &s;aved by him&mdash;But from whence came he? Even from Heaven, his Dwelling-Place, to this lower Earth, this Vale of Tears, <HI>to &s;eek and &s;ave that which was lo&s;t</HI>&mdash;All that feel them&s;elves lo&s;t, and are willing, like <HI>Zaccheus,</HI> to receive him into their Hearts&mdash;To &s;ave them&mdash;With how great a Salvation! Even from the Guilt, and al&s;o Power of their Sins&mdash;To make them Heirs of God, and Joint-Heirs with him&s;elf, and Partakers of that Glory, which he enjoyed with the Father before the World began&mdash;Thus will the <HI>Son of Man</HI> &s;ave that which is lo&s;t&mdash;He was made the <HI>Son of Man</HI> on purpo&s;e that he might &s;ave them&mdash;He had no other End but this in leaving his Father's
<PB N="215" REF="005311_0222_10181B6A2E6B4530">
Throne, in obeying the moral Law, and hanging upon the Cro&s;s&mdash;All that was done and &s;uffered only to &s;atisfy, and procure a Righteou&s;ne&s;s for poor, lo&s;t, undone Sinners, and that too with|out Re&s;pect of Per&s;ons&mdash;<HI>"That which was lo&s;t"</HI>&mdash;All of every Nation and Language, that feel, bewail, and are truly de&s;irous of being delivered from their lo&s;t State, the Son of Man came down to &s;eek and to &s;ave&mdash;For he is a God mighty, not only &s;o, but willing to &s;ave to the uttermo&s;t all tho&s;e that come to God thro' him&mdash;He will in no wi&s;e ca&s;t them out&mdash;For he is th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> &s;ame to Day, as he was Ye&s;terday. He comes now to Sinners, as well as formerly, and I hope hath &s;ent me out this Day to &s;eek, and under him, to bring home &s;ome of you, the lo&s;t Sheep of the Hou&s;e of <HI>I&s;rael</HI>&mdash;What &s;ay you? Shall I go home rejoycing? Saying, that many like Sheep have went a&s;tray, but they have now be|lieved on Je&s;us Chri&s;t, and &s;o returned home to the great Shepherd and Bi&s;hop of their Souls. If the Lord would be plea&s;ed thus to pro&s;per me in my Work, I care not how many Legali&s;ts and &s;elf-righteous <HI>Phari&s;ees</HI> murmur again&s;t me, for offering Salvation to the wor&s;t of Sinners&mdash;For I know the Son of Man came to &s;eek and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ave them, and the Lord Je&s;us will now be a Gue&s;t to the wor&s;t <HI>Publican,</HI> the vile&s;t Sinner that is among&s;t you, if he does but believe on him&mdash;Make ha&s;te then, O Sinners, make ha&s;te, and come by Faith to Chri&s;t&mdash;Then, this Day, even this Hour, nay, this Moment, if you believe<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> Je&s;us Chri&s;t &s;hall come, and make his eternal
<PB N="216" REF="005311_0223_10181B6C26DCC6B8">
Abode in your Hearts&mdash;Which of you is ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e willing to receive the King of Glory? Which of you obeys the Call, a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>Zaccheus</HI> did? Alas! why do you &s;tand &s;till? How know you wh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">+ther Je&s;us Chri&s;t may ever call you again? Come then, poor guilty Sinners&mdash;Come away, poor lo&s;t, undone <HI>Publicans</HI>&mdash;Make ha&s;te, I &s;ay, and come away to Je&s;us Chri&s;t&mdash;The Lord conde|&s;cends to invite him&s;elf to come under the filth&punc; Roofs of the Hou&s;es of your Souls&mdash;Do not be afraid of entertaining him&mdash;He will fill you with all Peace and Joy in Believing&mdash;Do not be a&s;hamed to run before the Multitude, and to have all Manner of Evil &s;poke again&s;t you fal&s;ely for his &s;ake&mdash;One Sight of Chri&s;t will make amends for all&mdash;<HI>Zaccheus</HI> was laughed at, and <HI>all that will live godly in Chri&s;t Je&s;us &s;hall &s;uffer Per&s;ecution?</HI> But what of that? <HI>Zaccheus</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> now crowned in Glory, as you al&s;o &s;hall &s;hortly be, if you believe on, and are reproached for Chri&s;t's &s;ake. Do not therefore put me off with frivolous Excu&s;es&mdash;There's no Excu&s;e can be given for your not coming to Chri&s;t&mdash;You are lo&s;t, undone, without him; and if he is not glorified in your Salvation, he will be glorified in your De&s;truction&mdash;If he does not come, and make his Abode in your Hearts, you mu&s;t take up an eternal Abode with the Devil and his An|gels&mdash;Oh that the Lord would be plea&s;ed to pa&s;s by &s;ome of you at this Time! Oh that he may call you by his Spirit; and make you a willing People in this Day of his Power! For I know my Calling will not do, unle&s;s He, by his effica|cious
<PB N="217" REF="005311_0224_10181B6F101848F8">
not, Grace, compell you to come in&mdash;Oh that you once felt what it is to receive Je&s;us Chri&s;t into your Hearts! You would &s;oon, like <HI>Zaccheus,</HI> give him every Thing&mdash;You do not love Chri&s;t, becau&s;e you do not know him&mdash;You do not come to him, becau&s;e you do not feel your Want of him&mdash;You are whole, and not broken-hearted&mdash;You are not &s;ick, at lea&s;t not &s;en&s;ible of your Sickne&s;s, and therefore no wonder you do not apply to Je&s;us Chri&s;t, that Great, that Almighty Phy&s;ician&mdash;You do not feel your &s;elves lo&s;t, and therefore do not &s;eek to be found in Chri&s;t&mdash;Oh that God would wound you with the Sword of his Spirit! Oh that he would cau&s;e his Arrows of Conviction to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> in your Heart, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Oh that he would dart a R<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">v of divine Light into your Souls&punc; For if you do not feel your &s;elves <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> Chri&s;t you are of all Men mo&s;t mi&s;erable&mdash;Your Souls are dea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">, you are not only an Image <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, but in &s;ome Degree Hell it &s;elf&mdash;You carry Hell about with you, and you know <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> no&mdash;Oh that I could &s;ee &s;ome of you &s;en&s;ible of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> and hear you cry out, <Q>Lord, break this hard Heart&mdash;Lord, deliver me from the Body of this Death&mdash;Draw me, Lord, make me willing to come after thee&mdash;I am lo&s;t&mdash;Lord, &s;ave me, or I peri&s;h</Q>&mdash;W<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters"> this your Ca&s;e, How <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> would the Lord &s;tretch forth by Almighty Hand, and &s;ay, Be of good Cheer, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> I, be not afraid&mdash;What a wonderful Ca<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="3 letters"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> your troubled Souls! Your <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> would <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> be with the Father and
<PB N="218" REF="005311_0225_10181B72114A9708">
the Son&mdash;Your Life would be hid with Chri&s;t in God&mdash;Some of you I hope have experienced this, and can &s;ay, I was lo&s;t, but I am found; I was dead, but am alive again&mdash;The Son of Man came and &s;ought me in the Day of his Power, and &s;aved my &s;inful Soul&mdash;And do you repent that you came to Chri&s;t? Has he not been a good Ma&s;ter? Is not his Pre&s;ence &s;weet to your Souls? Has he not been faithful to his Promi&s;e? And have you not found that even in doing and &s;uffering for him there is an exceeding pre&s;ent great Reward? I am per|&s;waded you will an&s;wer, Yes&mdash;Oh then, ye Saints, recommend and talk of the Love of Chri&s;t to others, and tell them, Oh tell them, what great Things the Lord has done for you!&mdash;This may encourage others to come unto him&mdash;And who knows, but the Lord may make you Fi&s;hers of Men? The Story of <HI>Zaccheus</HI> was left on Record for this Purpo&s;e&mdash;No truly convicted Soul, after &s;uch an In&s;tance of divine Grace has been laid before him, need de&s;pair of Mercy&mdash;What if you are <HI>Publicans?</HI> Was not <HI>Zaccheus</HI> a <HI>Publican?</HI> What if you are chief among the <HI>Publicans?</HI> Was not <HI>Zaccheus</HI> &s;o likewi&s;e? What if you are rich? Was not <HI>Zaccheus</HI> rich al&s;o? And yet Almighty Grace made him more than Conqueror over all the&s;e Hindrances&mdash;All Things are po&s;&s;ible to Je&s;us Chri&s;t; Nothing is too hard for Him&mdash;He is the Lord Almighty&mdash;Our Mountains of Sins mu&s;t all fall before this great <HI>Zerubbabel</HI>&mdash;On him God the Father has laid the Iniquities
<PB N="219" REF="005311_0226_10181B74EBB3A328">
of all that &s;hall believe on him, and in his own Body he bare them on the Tree&mdash;There, there by Faith, O Mou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">ners in <HI>Sion,</HI> may you &s;ee your Saviour hanging with Arms &s;tretched out, and hear him, as it were, thus &s;peaking to your Souls&mdash;<Q>Behold how I have loved you!&mdash;Behold my Hand<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter"> and my Feet!&mdash;Look, look into my wo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 letters">ded Side, and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> a Heart flaming with Love <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> &s;tronger than Death&mdash;Come into my Arms, O Sinners, come wa&s;h your <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> in my Heart's Blood&mdash;See here <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> for all Sin and all <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> how the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> you&mdash;Come, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> your &s;elves in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">&mdash;For I am <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">&mdash;I am <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> may <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> more&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the Serpent in the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> on a Tree&mdash;See <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> you&mdash;The <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> upon me. I am thus <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"></Q>
<PB N="220" REF="005311_0227_10181B76858EBAC0">
on him now&mdash;For tho' he is dead, he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;peak<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">|eth all this in the Scripture, nay, in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ays all this in the Words of the Text&mdash;<HI>The Son of Man is come to &s;eek and to &s;ave that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> was lo&s;t</HI>&mdash;Do not therefore any longer <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> the Lord of Glory&mdash;Bring tho&s;e Rebels, your Sins, which will not have him to reign over them&mdash;Bring them out to him&mdash;Tho' you cannot <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> them your&s;elves, yet he will &s;lay them for you&mdash;The Power of his Death and Re&s;urrection is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> great now as formerly&mdash;Make ha&s;te therefore, ma<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 letter">e ha&s;te, O ye Publicans and Sinners, and give the dear Lord Je&s;us your Hearts, your whole Hearts&mdash;If you refu&s;e to hearken to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Call of the Lord, remember your Damnation will be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> I am free from the Blood <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> you all&mdash;You <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> acquit my Ma&s;ter and me at the terrible Day <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> Judgment&mdash;Oh that you may know the Thing that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to your everla&s;ting Peace, be <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> they are eternally hid from your Eves! Let <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> that have the Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ay <HI>Amen.</HI></P>
